    "The main problem with this approach can be related to the integrity, privacy, and security of the data since they must be centralized for training purposes, so they will leave the device or institution that manages them.",
    "However, this is not the only issue, as centralizing data can sometimes be unfeasible from a technical or connectivity point of view or even due to legal restrictions.",
    "In this sense, the need arises to develop a learning architecture to deal with all these issues.",
    "On the one hand, we can solve problems related to computational issues using distributed learning.",
    "Regarding data security and privacy, in recent years there has been a boom in privacy-preserving ML architectures, which will be discussed in detail in the following, among which FL is particularly prominent (Asad et al. 2023)."
